e-workflow\",\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:2925:            f\"Invoking improve_library_coverage workflow for issue #{issue_number}: \"\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:2936:        rc = run_improve_library_coverage_workflow(pipeline_argv)\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:2942:                f\"ERROR: improve_library_coverage workflow failed for issue #{issue_number} (exit {rc})\",\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:3752:        run_make_pr_improve_coverage(\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:4869:        \"--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access\",\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:4872:            \"Forwarded to the new-library pipeline. Keeps generated tests for dynamic-access \"\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:4873:            \"strategies even when no dynamic-access coverage is added.\"\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:3:description: Review pull requests with the `fixes-java-run-fail` label in graalvm-reachability-metadata. Use when asked to review or triage a PR described as `fixes-java-run-fail` or one that fixes Java/JVM runtime test failures for an existing library version update. Focus on validating the Java runtime fix, keeping the diff scoped, and ensuring dynamic-access coverage does not drop between the previously tested version and the new version.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:9:These PRs repair tests, dependencies, or narrow runtime setup after an existing library version compiles, but the JVM-based test fails when it runs. Review them more lightly than `library-new-request` PRs: the library already exists, so the goal is to restore Java runtime behavior for the new version while preserving meaningful test and dynamic-access coverage.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:17:- Be more relaxed than `library-new-request`: do not reject only because a test resembles older coverage, stays in an existing package layout, or contains compatibility branches for multiple supported versions.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:18:- Do not accept changes that remove meaningful test coverage just to make `java` pass.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:20:- Treat dynamic-access coverage preservation as the main quality gate. The new version should not report lower dynamic-access coverage than the previously tested version unless the PR gives a concrete, credible reason.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:21:- For numeric gates, compare the reported evidence as-is. Do not inspect generation filters, agent configuration, or metadata contents to second-guess why dynamic-access or metadata-count numbers are what they are.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:56:4. Check dynamic-access coverage across versions.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:58:   - Compare `dynamicAccess.coverageRatio`, `coveredCalls`, `totalCalls`, and the `dynamicAccess.breakdown` entries for reflection, resources, proxies, serialization, JNI, or any other present report type.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:59:   - Do not use `user-code-filter.json`, agent configuration, or metadata file contents to argue that the reported dynamic-access values are not comparable. Use the stats values as reported unless the stats are missing or stale.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:60:   - A lower `coverageRatio` or lower `coveredCalls` for the new version is blocking unless the total dynamic-access surface changed and the PR explains why the reduction is expected.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:61:   - If `totalCalls` increases while `coveredCalls` stays flat or the ratio drops, ask for additional test coverage or metadata unless the uncovered calls are clearly outside the library behavior under test.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:69:   - Do not require an exact match. Differences are normal when upstream APIs move, generated metadata is cleaned up, or dynamic-access totals change.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:71:   - When the new total is below 25% of the original and the tests and dynamic-access stats still claim comparable coverage, ask for restored metadata or a concrete explanation of the API/runtime-surface change.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:77:   - Prefer seeing the full target `test` lane green because a Java runtime fix can still reduce native-image coverage.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:79:   - If CI is flaky but the diff and coverage comparison are sound, ask for a rerun instead of blocking on speculation.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:87:- Dynamic-access coverage does not drop between the previous and new tested versions, or any apparent drop is convincingly explained by a changed upstream API/runtime surface.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:95:- Dynamic-access coverage drops without a credible explanation and replacement coverage.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:103:- The API or runtime behavior change is plausible but the PR does not explain why a coverage drop is expected.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:110:- For coverage drops: say that dynamic-access coverage must not regress between tested versions, cite the old and new values, and ask for either restored coverage or a concrete explanation.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:112:- For deleted or bypassed coverage: say that the PR fixes Java runtime execution by removing coverage and should instead adapt the test to the new runtime behavior.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:114:- For native skips that does not depend on the open-ended dynamic class loading: say that the PR avoids the failing native path instead of fixing it, so it does not demonstrate native-image runtime coverage.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:3:description: Review pull requests with the `fixes-javac-fail` label in graalvm-reachability-metadata. Use when asked to review or triage a PR that fixes Java compilation failures for an existing library version update. Focus on validating the compile fix, keeping the diff scoped, and ensuring dynamic-access coverage does not drop between the previously tested version and the new version.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:9:These PRs repair test sources or test dependencies after an existing library is bumped and the new version no longer compiles with the old test code. Review them more lightly than `library-new-request` PRs: the library already exists, so the goal is to preserve working coverage across the version update rather than prove a brand-new metadata contribution from scratch.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:17:- Be more relaxed than `library-new-request`: do not reject only because a test resembles older coverage, stays in an existing package layout, or contains compatibility branches for multiple supported versions.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:18:- Do not accept changes that remove meaningful test coverage just to make `javac` pass.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:20:- Treat dynamic-access coverage preservation as the main quality gate. The new version should not report lower dynamic-access coverage than the previously tested version unless the PR gives a concrete, credible reason.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:21:- For numeric gates, compare the reported evidence as-is. Do not inspect generation filters, agent configuration, or metadata contents to second-guess why dynamic-access or metadata-count numbers are what they are.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:54:4. Check dynamic-access coverage across versions.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:56:   - Compare `dynamicAccess.coverageRatio`, `coveredCalls`, `totalCalls`, and the `dynamicAccess.breakdown` entries for reflection, resources, proxies, serialization, JNI, or any other present report type.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:57:   - Do not use `user-code-filter.json`, agent configuration, or metadata file contents to argue that the reported dynamic-access values are not comparable. Use the stats values as reported unless the stats are missing or stale.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:58:   - A lower `coverageRatio` or lower `coveredCalls` for the new version is blocking unless the total dynamic-access surface changed and the PR explains why the reduction is expected.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:59:   - If `totalCalls` increases while `coveredCalls` stays flat or the ratio drops, ask for additional test coverage or metadata unless the uncovered calls are clearly outside the library behavior under test.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:67:   - Do not require an exact match. Differences are normal when upstream APIs move, generated metadata is cleaned up, or dynamic-access totals change.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:69:   - When the new total is below 25% of the original and the tests and dynamic-access stats still claim comparable coverage, ask for restored metadata or a concrete explanation of the API/package change.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:74:   - Prefer seeing the full target `test` lane green because a compile fix can still reduce runtime or native coverage.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:76:   - If CI is flaky but the diff and coverage comparison are sound, ask for a rerun instead of blocking on speculation.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:84:- Dynamic-access coverage does not drop between the previous and new tested versions, or any apparent drop is convincingly explained by a changed upstream API surface.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:90:- The fix makes compilation pass by weakening or bypassing the test instead of adapting it to the changed API while preserving meaningful coverage.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:92:- Dynamic-access coverage drops without a credible explanation and replacement coverage.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:100:- The API change is plausible but the PR does not explain why a coverage drop is expected.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:107:- For coverage drops: say that dynamic-access coverage must not regress between tested versions, cite the old and new values, and ask for either restored coverage or a concrete explanation.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:109:- For deleted coverage: say that the PR fixes compilation by removing coverage and should instead adapt the test to the new API.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:110:- For native skips that does not depend on the open-ended dynamic class loading: say that the PR avoids the failing native path instead of fixing it, so it does not demonstrate native-image runtime coverage.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:121:- Bad compile repair that removes coverage:\n./README.md:3:<p><a href=\"COVERAGE.md\"><picture><source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\" srcset=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/dynamic/json.svg?label=supported%20libraries&query=%24.badges.librariesSupported&url=https%3A%2F%2Fraw.githubusercontent.com%2Foracle%2Fgraalvm-reachability-metadata%2Fstats%2Fcoverage%2Flatest%2Fbadges.json&style=flat&color=38BDF8&labelColor=1F2937\"><img alt=\"Supported libraries\" src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/dynamic/json.svg?label=supported%20libraries&query=%24.badges.librariesSupported&url=https%3A%2F%2Fraw.githubusercontent.com%2Foracle%2Fgraalvm-reachability-metadata%2Fstats%2Fcoverage%2Flatest%2Fbadges.json&style=flat&color=0A7EC2&labelColor=E5E7EB\"></picture></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"COVERAGE.md\"><picture><source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\" srcset=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/dynamic/json.svg?label=tested%20library%20versions&query=%24.badges.testedLibraryVersions&url=https%3A%2F%2Fraw.githubusercontent.com%2Foracle%2Fgraalvm-reachability-metadata%2Fstats%2Fcoverage%2Flatest%2Fbadges.json&style=flat&color=F59E0B&labelColor=1F2937\"><img alt=\"Tested library versions\" src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/dynamic/json.svg?label=tested%20library%20versions&query=%24.badges.testedLibraryVersions&url=https%3A%2F%2Fraw.githubusercontent.com%2Foracle%2Fgraalvm-reachability-metadata%2Fstats%2Fcoverage%2Flatest%2Fbadges.json&style=flat&color=BF8700&labelColor=E5E7EB\"></picture></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"COVERAGE.md\"><picture><source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\" srcset=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/dynamic/json.svg?label=dynamic%20access%20coverage&query=%24.badges.dynamicAccessCoverage&url=https%3A%2F%2Fraw.githubusercontent.com%2Foracle%2Fgraalvm-reachability-metadata%2Fstats%2Fcoverage%2Flatest%2Fbadges.json&style=flat&color=34D399&labelColor=1F2937\"><img alt=\"Dynamic access coverage\" src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/dynamic/json.svg?label=dynamic%20access%20coverage&query=%24.badges.dynamicAccessCoverage&url=https%3A%2F%2Fraw.githubusercontent.com%2Foracle%2Fgraalvm-reachability-metadata%2Fstats%2Fcoverage%2Flatest%2Fbadges.json&style=flat&color=1F9D55&labelColor=E5E7EB\"></picture></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"COVERAGE.md\"><picture><source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\" srcset=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/dynamic/json.svg?label=tested%20LoC&query=%24.badges.testedLinesOfCode&url=https%3A%2F%2Fraw.githubusercontent.com%2Foracle%2Fgraalvm-reachability-metadata%2Fstats%2Fcoverage%2Flatest%2Fbadges.json&style=flat&color=FB923C&labelColor=1F2937\"><img alt=\"Tested LoC\" src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/dynamic/json.svg?label=tested%20LoC&query=%24.badges.testedLinesOfCode&url=https%3A%2F%2Fraw.githubusercontent.com%2Foracle%2Fgraalvm-reachability-metadata%2Fstats%2Fcoverage%2Flatest%2Fbadges.json&style=flat&color=C2410C&labelColor=E5E7EB\"></picture></a></p>\n./skills/README.md:22:It covers new-library metadata PRs, including titles like `[GenAI] Add support for com.fasterxml:classmate:1.5.1 using gpt-5.4`, and encodes the review rules already used in this repository: reject scaffold-only tests, keep test packages separate from library packages so tests do not bypass visibility boundaries, and question metadata coverage claims that are not supported by the diff.\n./skills/README.md:27:It covers compile-failure repair PRs for existing libraries and applies a lighter review than `library-new-request`: keep the diff scoped to the compile fix, preserve meaningful tests, and block regressions where dynamic-access coverage drops between the previously tested version and the new version.\n./skills/README.md:32:It covers JVM runtime-failure repair PRs for existing libraries and applies a lighter review than `library-new-request`: keep the diff scoped to the Java runtime fix, preserve meaningful tests and assertions, and block regressions where dynamic-access coverage drops between the previously tested version and the new version.\n./skills/README.md:37:It covers native-image runtime-failure repair PRs for existing libraries and applies a lighter review than `library-new-request`: verify the native path is fixed rather than skipped, keep metadata and test changes scoped, and block regressions where dynamic-access coverage drops between the previously tested version and the new version.\n./forge/ai_workflows/fix_java_run_fail.py:13:    [--strategy-name \"java_run_iterative_with_coverage_sources_pi_gpt-5.5\"] \\\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:22:| **Repository automation (Metadata Forge)** | Generate or repair metadata using LLM-driven pipelines. | Per coordinate, the toolkit can: (1) **add support for a new library** — generate a JUnit / Kotlin / Scala test suite, scaffold metadata, and iterate until JVM-mode tests pass and dynamic-access is collected ([`add_new_library_support.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/add_new_library_support.py)); (2) **fix a Java compilation (`javac`) failure** raised by a library version bump ([`fix_javac_fail.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_javac_fail.py)); (3) **fix a JVM-mode (`javaTest`) runtime failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_java_run_fail.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_java_run_fail.py)); (4) **fix a `native-image` runtime failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_ni_run.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_ni_run.py)); (5) **improve dynamic-access coverage** of already-supported libraries by targeting uncovered call sites; (6) **post-generation repair** of the metadata produced by a previous run ([`fix_post_generation_pi.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_post_generation_pi.py), [`fix_metadata_codex.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_metadata_codex.py)). Each task runs Gradle tasks against a worktree of this repo, appends a schema-validated metrics record, and — when invoked through [`forge/git_scripts/make_pr_*.py`](../forge/git_scripts/) — opens a PR for human review. See [forge/docs/architecture.md](../forge/docs/architecture.md). |\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:46:- A `stats/<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/stats.json` mirror of per-version metrics (dynamic-access call sites, coverage, lines of code, dependency information).\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:55:- Coverage collection (JaCoCo) and dynamic-access reporting per coordinate.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:63:- Schedule-driven: full metadata sweep, new-library-version compatibility (every 4 hours), Docker image vulnerability scans, scheduled release every two weeks, scheduled coverage publication.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:73:`publish-scheduled-coverage.yml` derives, from committed `stats/` and `metadata/**/index.json`:\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:74:- `latest/badges.json` — badges shown in the README (libraries supported, tested versions, dynamic-access coverage, tested LOC).\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:79:These are force-pushed to the `stats/coverage` branch.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:84:1. **Add new library support** — generate a JUnit test suite, scaffold metadata, iterate until JVM-mode tests pass and dynamic-access metadata is collected.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:87:4. **Improve coverage** of already-supported libraries by targeting uncovered dynamic-access call sites.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:98:| `library-update-request` | Issue / PR | Request or PR to improve support for an already-covered library, including coverage-improvement work. |\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:217:- **FR-T-7** Dynamic-access coverage between consecutive tested versions of a library must not regress (enforced by reviewer skills `review-fixes-javac-fail`, `review-fixes-native-image-run-fail`, `review-fixes-java-run-fail`).\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:256:- **NFR-7 Auditability.** Every Forge run produces a schema-validated metrics record; every coverage publish writes to a force-pushed branch with retained history.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:271:- Mirrored stats under `stats/` and aggregated coverage artifacts on `stats/coverage`.\n./forge/ai_workflows/java_fail_workflow.py:39:DEFAULT_JAVAC_STRATEGY = \"javac_iterative_with_coverage_sources_pi_gpt-5.5\"\n./forge/ai_workflows/java_fail_workflow.py:40:DEFAULT_JAVA_RUN_STRATEGY = \"java_run_iterative_with_coverage_sources_pi_gpt-5.5\"\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:29:To run the same coverage with future defaults enabled:\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:145:Generate coverage for the library under test exercised by our tests. Report contains coverage that focus exclusively on the provided library JARs, excluding unrelated external dependencies.\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:318:- Generate dynamic access coverage report: `./gradlew generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]`\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:319:  Output: `metadata/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/test/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`\n./forge/ai_workflows/add_new_library_support.py:141:        \"--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access\",\n./forge/ai_workflows/add_new_library_support.py:144:            \"When using dynamic-access strategies, keep generated tests even when they do not improve \"\n./forge/ai_workflows/add_new_library_support.py:145:            \"dynamic-access coverage.\"\n./forge/ai_workflows/add_new_library_support.py:151:        help=\"Enable resumable large-library chunking for dynamic-access workflows.\",\n./stats/org.bouncycastle/bcpkix-jdk15to18/1.77/stats.json:7:          \"coverageRatio\" : 0.0,\n./stats/org.bouncycastle/bcpkix-jdk15to18/1.77/stats.json:12:          \"coverageRatio\" : 0.0,\n./stats/org.bouncycastle/bcpkix-jdk15to18/1.77/stats.json:17:      \"coverageRatio\" : 0.0,\n./forge/ai_workflows/improve_library_coverage.py:6:\"\"\"Workflow entry point for improving dynamic-access coverage on an existing library.\n./forge/ai_workflows/improve_library_coverage.py:9:focuses solely on generating new tests to improve dynamic-access coverage.\n./forge/ai_workflows/improve_library_coverage.py:12:  python3 ai_workflows/improve_library_coverage.py \\\n./forge/ai_workflows/improve_library_coverage.py:56:METRICS_TASK_TYPE = \"improve_library_coverage\"\n./forge/ai_workflows/improve_library_coverage.py:73:        prog=\"improve_library_coverage.py\",\n./forge/ai_workflows/improve_library_coverage.py:74:        description=\"Improve dynamic-access coverage for an existing library version.\",\n./forge/ai_workflows/improve_library_coverage.py:112:        help=\"Enable resumable large-library chunking for dynamic-access workflows.\",\n./forge/ai_workflows/improve_library_coverage.py:244:    new_branch = build_ai_branch_name(f\"improve-coverage-{group}-{artifact}-{version}\")\n./forge/ai_workflows/improve_library_coverage.py:273:        [\"git\", \"commit\", \"--allow-empty\", \"-m\", f\"Checkpoint for coverage improvement of {library}\"],\n./forge/ai_workflows/improve_library_coverage.py:358:        task_type=\"improve-library-coverage\",\n./forge/ai_workflows/fix_java_fails.py:26:DEFAULT_JAVAC_STRATEGY = \"javac_iterative_with_coverage_sources_pi_gpt-5.5\"\n./forge/ai_workflows/fix_java_fails.py:27:DEFAULT_JAVA_RUN_STRATEGY = \"java_run_iterative_with_coverage_sources_pi_gpt-5.5\"\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/__init__.py:10:from ai_workflows.workflow_strategies.increase_dynamic_access_coverage_strategy import IncreaseDynamicAccessCoverageStrategy\n./forge/utility_scripts/jacoco_parser.py:7:JaCoCo XML coverage parser.\n./forge/utility_scripts/jacoco_parser.py:8:Parses lines coverage from JaCoCo XML and aggregates all <counter type='LINE'> elements.\n./forge/utility_scripts/jacoco_parser.py:19:def compute_line_coverage(xml_path: str):\n./forge/utility_scripts/jacoco_parser.py:21:    Aggregate line counters from a JaCoCo XML report and return coverage percent.\n./forge/utility_scripts/jacoco_parser.py:57:    percent, covered_total = compute_line_coverage(xml_path)\n./stats/org.bouncycastle/bcpkix-jdk18on/1.77/stats.json:7:          \"coverageRatio\" : 0.0,\n./stats/org.bouncycastle/bcpkix-jdk18on/1.77/stats.json:12:          \"coverageRatio\" : 0.0,\n./stats/org.bouncycastle/bcpkix-jdk18on/1.77/stats.json:17:      \"coverageRatio\" : 0.0,\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/workflow_strategy.py:255:        # Full CI-matrix GraalVM coverage, including GRAALVM_HOME_25_0, runs in\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/increase_dynamic_access_coverage_strategy.py:14:@WorkflowStrategy.register(\"increase_dynamic_access_coverage\")\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/increase_dynamic_access_coverage_strategy.py:16:    \"\"\"Composite strategy that runs a primary workflow then improves dynamic-access coverage.\"\"\"\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/increase_dynamic_access_coverage_strategy.py:39:            self._print_message(\"no primary workflow configured, skipping to dynamic-access coverage phase\")\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/increase_dynamic_access_coverage_strategy.py:50:                self._print_message(\"skipping dynamic-access coverage phase because primary workflow did not succeed\")\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/increase_dynamic_access_coverage_strategy.py:56:        self._print_message(\"starting dynamic-access coverage phase\")\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_